export const docsGuide = {"categories":[{"title":"Getting started","stories":[{"id":"sign-in","title":"Sign in with OpenApe","introHtml":"<p>Troop is a DDISA Service Provider: it discovers your IdP from your email domain via a DNS TXT record and redirects you there to authorize — no password, no per-app account.</p>\n","steps":[{"title":"Open Troop","html":"The start page has the sign-in right there: enter your email.","shot":"/docs/screenshots/sign-in/01-landing.png"},{"title":"Authorize at your IdP","html":"Troop redirects you to your IdP, which asks once whether Troop may use your identity. Approve — the decision is remembered.","shot":"/docs/screenshots/sign-in/02-consent.png"},{"title":"You are in","html":"Back on Troop, authenticated: the agents dashboard. From here you spawn, configure and talk to your agents.","shot":"/docs/screenshots/sign-in/03-dashboard.png"}]}]},{"title":"Agents","stories":[{"id":"spawn-agent","title":"Spawn your first agent","introHtml":"<p>Agents run on YOUR machine: a local nest daemon is bound to Troop and receives spawn intents over a websocket. Spawning creates a real OS user, an agent identity at your IdP, and a chat bridge.</p>\n","steps":[{"title":"Open the spawn dialog","html":"Hit <strong>Spawn agent</strong> in the dashboard. Name and system prompt are the base of every agent; a quick-start <strong>preset</strong> (calendar assistant, mail triage, daily summary, …) pre-fills the prompt — or keep <em>Custom (empty)</em> and write your own.","shot":"/docs/screenshots/spawn-agent/01-dialog.png"},{"title":"Name it and write the prompt — a custom agent","html":"This is a <strong>custom agent</strong>: its behaviour comes entirely from the system prompt you write here (you can refine it later on the agent&#39;s page). Model and key are optional — without them the agent uses your nest&#39;s default LLM.","shot":"/docs/screenshots/spawn-agent/02-custom-agent.png"},{"title":"Or attach a recipe instead","html":"A <strong>recipe agent</strong> gets its intent, tools and schedule from a pinned repository (<code>github.com/&lt;owner&gt;/&lt;repo&gt;@&lt;ref&gt;</code>). Pick a curated one — here <em>Bluesky feed summary</em>, which pins its repo and pre-declares the secrets it needs — or paste your own pinned repo via <em>Custom…</em>. The recipe is <em>additive</em>: your system prompt rides along on top of the recipe&#39;s intent. Skip it for a pure custom agent.","shot":"/docs/screenshots/spawn-agent/03-recipe-option.png"},{"title":"Spawn","html":"Troop forwards the intent to your nest, which provisions the agent. Within seconds it shows up in <strong>My Agents</strong> — it now has its own identity at your IdP (<code>&lt;name&gt;-…@id.openape.ai</code>) and is reachable from every OpenApe app.","shot":"/docs/screenshots/spawn-agent/04-spawned.png"}]},{"id":"chat-with-agent","title":"Chat with your agent","introHtml":"<p>Every agent has a chat. A reply proves the whole path end-to-end: Troop → nest → bridge → LLM → back.</p>\n","steps":[{"title":"Send a message","html":"Open the agent and type a message. The bridge picks it up over the websocket and runs your configured LLM.","shot":null},{"title":"The agent replies","html":"The reply lands in the chat — in this E2E run it is tagged <code>[mock-llm]</code>, proving spawn → bridge → LLM → reply without touching a paid model.","shot":"/docs/screenshots/chat-with-agent/02-reply.png"}]},{"id":"inspect-agent","title":"Inspect & configure an agent","introHtml":"<p>The agent page is also its control panel: system prompt, schedule, tools and run history live next to the chat.</p>\n","steps":[{"title":"Open the agent page","html":"Edit the system prompt, set a cron schedule for recurring runs, pick tools, or wire a recipe — changes sync to the nest live over the websocket.","shot":"/docs/screenshots/inspect-agent/01-detail.png"}]},{"id":"destroy-agent","title":"Destroy an agent","introHtml":"<p>Tearing an agent down removes the OS user on the nest and de-registers its identity at the IdP — no zombie credentials.</p>\n","steps":[{"title":"Destroy it","html":"Hit <strong>Destroy</strong> on the agent (or <code>apes agents destroy &lt;name&gt;</code>). The nest wipes the agent home and the IdP drops its identity.","shot":null},{"title":"Gone","html":"The dashboard is empty again — spawn → run → destroy, fully reversible.","shot":"/docs/screenshots/destroy-agent/02-gone.png"}]}]}]}
